{"title_page": "Coronavirus (Scotland) Act 2020", "text_new": "{{Infobox UK legislation\n|short_title            = Coronavirus (Scotland) Act 2020\n|parliament             = Scottish Parliament\n|type                   = Scottish Act\n|long_title             = An Act of the Scottish Parliament to make provision in connection with coronavirus; and for connected purposes.\n|statute_book_chapter   = 2020 asp 7\n|introduced_by          = [[Michael Russell (politician)|Michael Russell]] [[Member of the Scottish Parliament|MSP]]\n|territorial_extent     = [[Scotland]]\n|royal_assent           = 6 April 2020\n|commencement           = \n|repeal_date            =\n|amendments             =\n|related_legislation    = [[Coronavirus Act 2020]]\n|repealing_legislation  =\n|status                 = current\n|original_text          = http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2020/7/pdfs/asp_20200007_en.pdf\n|revised_text           = \n|legislation_history    = \n|}}\n\nThe '''Coronavirus (Scotland) Act 2020''' is an Act of the [[Scottish Parliament]] to make provisions during the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Scotland|COVID-19 pandemic]]. The Act complements and regulates the use of emergency powers given to [[Scottish Government|Scottish Ministers]] under the [[UK Parliament]]'s [[Coronavirus Act 2020]]. The Act makes many provisions to ease regulations in sectors that may struggle to meet their statutory requirements, such as the [[NHS Scotland|NHS]], [[Social Security Scotland]] and the [[Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scottishlegal.com/article/evictions-ban-outlined-as-emergency-legislation-moves-forward|title=Evictions ban outlined as emergency legislation moves forward|last=News|first=Scottish Legal|website=Scottish Legal News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Provisions==\nThe Act makes a variety of provisions to ensure continuity throughout Scotland during the Coronavirus pandemic. This covers a broad variety of issues within Scotland where it would be impossible for statutory requirements to be met or where regulations have become unworkable, notably in terms of:<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-52111412|title=MSPs agree emergency coronavirus powers|date=2020-04-01|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-08|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n*Housing provision and evictions\n*[[Social Security Scotland]] assessments\n*Judicial operations\n*Healthcare regulations\n*Death certification\n*Miscellaneous provisions\n\n===Time limit and renewal===\nPart 1 of the Act expires on 30 September 2020, however Scottish Ministers can extent the act twice on a six-monthly basis. This can only be achieved through affirmation of the Scottish Parliament.\n\n==Debate==\nThe Act was developed by the [[Scottish Government]] on a cross-party basis to ensure maximum support. Concerns were raised at the prospect of removing the requirement of [[Trial by jury in Scotland|juries within judicial trials]]. This was accepted by the government and removed from the bill before passage. The Bill was passed unanimously.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theedinburghreporter.co.uk/2020/04/coronavirus-bill-passed-at-holyrood/ |title=Coronavirus Bill passed at Holyrood |website=www.theedinburghreporter.co.uk |access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Legislative history==\nThe bill was introduced to Parliament on 31 March 2020 as an Emergency Bill, with all three legislative stages completed the following day. The Bill was given Royal Assent and made law on 6 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eveningexpress.co.uk/news/scotland/emergency-coronavirus-bill-given-royal-assent-in-just-five-days/|title=Emergency coronavirus Bill given royal assent in just five days|last=Association|first=Press|date=2020-04-06|website=Evening Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Coronavirus Act 2020]]\n*[[COVID-19 pandemic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:Acts of the Scottish Parliament 2020]]\n[[Category:2020 in Scotland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Law associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n\n\n{{Scots-law-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox UK legislation\n|short_title            = Coronavirus (Scotland) Act 2020\n|parliament             = Scottish Parliament\n|type                   = Scottish Act\n|long_title             = An Act of the Scottish Parliament to make provision in connection with coronavirus; and for connected purposes.\n|statute_book_chapter   = 2020 asp 7\n|introduced_by          = [[Michael Russell (politician)|Michael Russell]] [[Member of the Scottish Parliament|MSP]]\n|territorial_extent     = [[Scotland]]\n|royal_assent           = 6 April 2020\n|commencement           = \n|repeal_date            =\n|amendments             =\n|related_legislation    = [[Coronavirus Act 2020]]\n|repealing_legislation  =\n|status                 = current\n|original_text          = http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2020/7/pdfs/asp_20200007_en.pdf\n|revised_text           = \n|legislation_history    = \n|}}\n\nThe '''Coronavirus (Scotland) Act 2020''' is an Act of the [[Scottish Parliament]] to make provisions during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Scotland|COVID-19 pandemic]]. The Act complements and regulates the use of emergency powers given to [[Scottish Government|Scottish Ministers]] under the [[UK Parliament]]'s [[Coronavirus Act 2020]]. The Act makes many provisions to ease regulations in sectors that may struggle to meet their statutory requirements, such as the [[NHS Scotland|NHS]], [[Social Security Scotland]] and the [[Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scottishlegal.com/article/evictions-ban-outlined-as-emergency-legislation-moves-forward|title=Evictions ban outlined as emergency legislation moves forward|last=News|first=Scottish Legal|website=Scottish Legal News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Provisions==\nThe Act makes a variety of provisions to ensure continuity throughout Scotland during the Coronavirus pandemic. This covers a broad variety of issues within Scotland where it would be impossible for statutory requirements to be met or where regulations have become unworkable, notably in terms of:<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-52111412|title=MSPs agree emergency coronavirus powers|date=2020-04-01|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-08|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n*Housing provision and evictions\n*[[Social Security Scotland]] assessments\n*Judicial operations\n*Healthcare regulations\n*Death certification\n*Miscellaneous provisions\n\n===Time limit and renewal===\nPart 1 of the Act expires on 30 September 2020, however Scottish Ministers can extent the act twice on a six-monthly basis. This can only be achieved through affirmation of the Scottish Parliament.\n\n==Debate==\nThe Act was developed by the [[Scottish Government]] on a cross-party basis to ensure maximum support. Concerns were raised at the prospect of removing the requirement of [[Trial by jury in Scotland|juries within judicial trials]]. This was accepted by the government and removed from the bill before passage. The Bill was passed unanimously.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theedinburghreporter.co.uk/2020/04/coronavirus-bill-passed-at-holyrood/ |title=Coronavirus Bill passed at Holyrood |website=www.theedinburghreporter.co.uk |access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Legislative history==\nThe bill was introduced to Parliament on 31 March 2020 as an Emergency Bill, with all three legislative stages completed the following day. The Bill was given Royal Assent and made law on 6 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eveningexpress.co.uk/news/scotland/emergency-coronavirus-bill-given-royal-assent-in-just-five-days/|title=Emergency coronavirus Bill given royal assent in just five days|last=Association|first=Press|date=2020-04-06|website=Evening Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Coronavirus Act 2020]]\n*[[COVID-19 pandemic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:Acts of the Scottish Parliament 2020]]\n[[Category:2020 in Scotland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Law associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n\n\n{{Scots-law-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "RobertskySemi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:bypass redirect, replaced:Scottish Parliamentto make provisions during theCOVID-19 pandemic. The Act complements and regulates the use of emergency powers given to [[Scottish Government|Scott", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus_(Scotland)_Act_2020"}
